One person was injured when a fire broke out at a business premises in Alexander Road in Westmead in Pinetown, Durban late on Friday afternoon, paramedics said.
Rescue Care paramedics arrived on the scene at about 5pm to find the Durban Fire Department in attendance fighting the blaze, Rescue Care spokesman Garrith Jamieson said on Saturday.

Smoke was billowing from the building. The fire was quickly contained by firefighters. One person sustained injuries and was stabilised on the scene before being transported by Rescue Care to a nearby hospital for further care.
At this stage the events leading up to the fire were unknown, but police and the Durban Fire Department would investigate, Jamieson said.
– African News Agency (ANA)
